izontal metric banner or timeline visualization, located near the search filters or integrated with the ticket list, to provide a richer overview. This integration will provide the user a better experience. Also, I am taking a look at the data to analyze how many tickets are available by default.\n\n\n**Refining Visual Priority**\n\nI'm now refining ticket priority visuals to reflect severity. I will standardize `P1` as red, `P2` as amber, and `P3` as cyan/blue for consistent communication. These changes will provide instant insights for the support team. I'm updating the component now to reflect the enhanced priority states.\n\n\n**Implementing Priority Badges**\n\nI'm now implementing dynamic priority badge styling using a helper function for clarity, with P1 as red, P2 as amber, and P3 as cyan, for instant issue severity recognition, enhancing overall visual clarity. This code aligns with established design principles for visual hierarchy and responsiveness.\n\n```\n\n\n**Refactoring Status Badges**\n\nI'm now refactoring the ticket status badge rendering. I'm writing a helper function to streamline the CSS classes for consistency and maintainability. This is an improvement to the code. The helper will consolidate styling for `RESOLVED`, `INVESTIGATING`, and `HOLD` states, resulting in a cleaner and more manageable implementation.\n\n\n**Enhancing Status Visuals**\n\nI'm now implementing the refactored status badge. I'm leveraging the helper function to consistently style `OPEN`, `RESOLVED`, `INVESTIGATING`, and `HOLD` states, ensuring a high-contrast premium tag design with a subtle border and pill background. I'm focusing on consistency. This should provide improved visual clarity and maintainability for the admin dashboard.\n\n\n**Polishing SLA Display**\n\nI'm now revising the SLA countdown display for enhanced clarity and premium aesthetics. I'm focusing on incorporating visual cues for different states: a \"SECURE\" badge with a check for resolved tickets, flashing red \"VIOLATED [OVERDUE]\" for expired SLAs, an orange \"RISK [timer]\" with an alarm icon for imminent violations, and a calm cyan timer otherwise. I aim for improved readability, and a more user-friendly interface.\n\n\n**Implementing SLA Visualization**\n\nI'm now integrating the SLA display with flashing indicators.  I've defined visual states using custom CSS to show the state. Implemented for improved readability. I will show a \"SECURE\" badge, a flashing \"VIOLATED [OVERDUE]\" badge, and an orange \"RISK [timer]\" with a clock.\n\n\n"}}
