{"ts":"2026-06-27T07:48:17.750Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing the Interface Design**\n\nOkay, I'm now zeroing in on lines 517-558 within the codebase. It seems like I'm dealing with the mobile display component. Specifically, there's a React component that renders tickets in a grid layout. The code snippet showcases how ticket information is handled, and rendered in a grid layout on smaller screens. I'm focusing on the click handler and how the `selectedTicketId` state is modified.\n\n\n**Examining the Rendering Logic**\n\nI'm now deep-diving into the JSX that renders each ticket within the grid. The focus is on the conditional class names. I'm trying to determine how visual styles change based on the `selectedTicketId` state and ticket properties like `status`. The `formatSla` function is key to the display of the SLA timer, and I'm interested in how it formats time based on ticket status.\n\n\n**Investigating the UI Component**\n\nI'm now analyzing the ticket details pane's rendering. Specifically, lines 580 to 590 are of interest. I'm focusing on the component that displays the ticket ID, subject, and client, along with the close button within the right-side drawer. It's becoming clearer how the selected ticket data is passed in, and how the close button updates state.\n\n\n**Evaluating the Conditional Classes**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the conditional class names within the ticket rendering loop. Specifically, I'm examining how the application styles individual tickets based on `selectedTicketId` and other ticket properties like `status`. The interplay between `hover`, `focus` states, and the `border` styling is critical for understanding the visual feedback.\n\n\n**Dissecting the Ticket Rendering**\n\nI'm now focusing on the JSX responsible for individual ticket representation within the grid, particularly the rendering of ticket details such as priority badges, subject lines, and client information. I am considering the style classes and the impact of the `getPriorityBadgeStyles` function, understanding that the design hinges on the dynamic styling of each element. I'm also examining the status display and SLA badge rendering.\n\n\n**Pinpointing the Close Button**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the close button's functionality within the ticket details pane. The JSX code includes a function setting `setSelectedTicketId(null)`, which is the central to closing the ticket details pane and clearing the selection. I'm noting how the button's visual style and its event handler are connected within the provided snippet. I am now understanding the use of inline styles.\n\n\n**Observing the Animation Styles**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the SVG animation styles related to the telemetry bridge status indicator. The code defines CSS keyframes and classes for fast, normal, and slow animation speeds by adjusting the `stroke-dasharray` and `stroke-dashoffset`. The animation uses `flowParticle` to create a flowing effect, and I am noting how the color changes depend on the selected ticket's status.\n\n\n**Interpreting the Ticket Indicators**\n\nI'm currently focusing on how visual cues are used to represent ticket information. I'm examining the conditional styling applied to priority badges and status displays, including color variations and animation effects. The logic for styling the animation based on `priority` and `status` is becoming clear.\n\n\n**Analyzing the SVG Details**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the SVG rendering logic, particularly the conditional attributes related to the flow animation and the node's fill and stroke colors. The styling of the telemetry bridge based on `selectedTicket.status` and `selectedTicket.priority` is crucial. I'm focusing on the interplay of `stroke-dasharray`, `stroke-dashoffset`, and fill colors based on the ticket's state. I'm noting the use of conditional styling and animation classes.\n\n\n**Deciphering the Status Node**\n\nI'm currently focused on the Admin node's logic within the SVG. The colors are conditionally set based on `selectedTicket.status` and `selectedTicket.assignedAgent`, which is used to indicate resolution and assignment status. I'm now understanding how the visual cues help clarify different ticket states, focusing on the fill and stroke of the circles.\n\n\n**Examining the SVG Elements**\n\nI'm now diving into the details of the SVG elements. I'm focusing on the textual data displayed within the SVG, specifically the \"TERMINAL\" label and the \"ATTESTATION_OFF\" or \"TLS_1.3_SECURE\" labels. The conditional rendering, using `selectedTicket.status`, determines which text is displayed, and I'm interested in how these elements dynamically reflect the ticket's state. I'm noting the use of fill colors.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T07:48:17.754Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"i572nwj7","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/admin/support/page.tsx","old_text":"      <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 md:hidden\">\n        {filteredTickets.map((t) => (\n          <div key={t.id} onClick={() => setSelectedTicketId(t.id)} className={`border rounded-xl p-4 space-y-3 bg-[#050505]/40 backdrop-blur-sm cursor-pointer ${selectedTicketId === t.id ? \"border-[#009DFF]\" : \"border-white/5\"}`}>\n            <div className=\"flex justify-between\">\n              <span className=\"text-[#009DFF] font-bold font-mono text-[11px]\">{t.id}</span>\n              <span className=\"text-white/40 font-mono text-[9px] uppercase\">{t.category}</span>\n            </div>\n            <h4 className=\"text-white font-semibold text-xs leading-snug\">{t.subject}</h4>\n            <div className=\"flex justify-between items-center pt-2 border-t border-white/5 font-mono text-[10px] text-white/50\">\n              <span>SLA TIMER:</span>\n              <span className={t.status === \"RESOLVED\" ? \"text-emerald-400 font-bold\" : \"text-amber-400 font-bold\"}>{formatSla(t.slaSeconds, t.status)}</span>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        ))}\n      </div>\n\n      {selectedTicket && (\n        <>\n          <div onClick={() => setSelectedTicketId(null)} className=\"fixed inset-0 bg-black/60 backdrop-blur-sm z-40 transition-all\" />\n          <div className=\"fixed inset-y-0 right-0 z-50 w-full sm:w-[500px] md:w-[600px] bg-[#070708] border-l border-white/10 shadow-2xl p-6 overflow-y-auto flex flex-col justify-between\">\n            <div className=\"space-y-5\">\n              <div className=\"flex justify-between items-start border-b border-white/5 pb-3\">\n                <div>\n                  <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-[#009DFF] bg-[#009DFF]/10 border border-[#009DFF]/20 px-2 py-0.5 rounded font-bold\">{selectedTicket.id}</span>\n                  <h3 className=\"text-sm font-bold text-white mt-2 leading-snug\">{selectedTicket.subject}</h3>\n                  <p className=\"text-[9.5px] font-mono text-white/40 uppercase mt-1\">CLIENT: {selectedTicket.client}</p>\n                </div>\n                <button onClick={() => setSelectedTicketId(null)} className=\"p-1 hover:bg-white/5 rounded text-white/40 cursor-pointer\"><X className=\"w-5 h-5\" /></button>\n              </div>\n\n              <div className=\"flex border-b border-white/5 font-mono text-[9.5px] select-none\">","new_text":"      <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 md:hidden\">\n        {filteredTickets.map((t) => (\n          <div \n            key={t.id} \n            onClick={() => setSelectedTicketId(t.id)} \n            onKeyDown={(e) => {\n              if (e.key === \"Enter\" || e.key === \" \") {\n                e.preventDefault();\n                setSelectedTicketId(t.id);\n              }\n            }}\n            tabIndex={0}\n            role=\"button\"\n            aria-pressed={selectedTicketId === t.id}\n            className={`border rounded-xl p-4 space-y-3 bg-[#050505]/40 backdrop-blur-sm cursor-pointer hover:bg-[#050505]/60 focus:border-[#009DFF] outline-none transition-all ${selectedTicketId === t.id ? \"border-[#009DFF]\" : \"border-white/5\"}`}\n          >\n            <div className=\"flex justify-between items-center\">\n              <span className=\"text-[#009DFF] font-bold font-mono text-[11px]\">{t.id}</span>\n              <span className={`inline-flex px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded border text-[8px] font-bold ${getPriorityBadgeStyles(t.priority)}`}>\n                {t.priority}\n              </span>\n            </div>\n            <h4 className=\"text-white font-semibold text-xs leading-snug\">{t.subject}</h4>\n            <p className=\"text-[9.5px] font-mono text-white/30 uppercase mt-1\">{t.client.split(\" [\")[0]}</p>\n            <div className=\"flex justify-between items-center pt-2 border-t border-white/5 font-mono text-[10px]\">\n              <span className=\"text-white/40 uppercase\">STATUS: {t.status}</span>\n              <span>{renderSlaBadge(t)}</span>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        ))}\n      </div>\n\n      {selectedTicket && (\n        <>\n          <div onClick={() => setSelectedTicketId(null)} className=\"fixed inset-0 bg-black/60 backdrop-blur-sm z-40 transition-all\" />\n          <div className=\"fixed inset-y-0 right-0 z-50 w-full sm:w-[500px] md:w-[600px] bg-[#070708] border-l border-white/10 shadow-2xl p-6 overflow-y-auto flex flex-col justify-between\">\n            <div className=\"space-y-5\">\n              <div className=\"flex justify-between items-start border-b border-white/5 pb-3\">\n                <div>\n                  <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-[#009DFF] bg-[#009DFF]/10 border border-[#009DFF]/20 px-2 py-0.5 rounded font-bold\">{selectedTicket.id}</span>\n                  <h3 className=\"text-sm font-bold text-white mt-2 leading-snug\">{selectedTicket.subject}</h3>\n                  <p className=\"text-[9.5px] font-mono text-white/40 uppercase mt-1\">CLIENT: {selectedTicket.client}</p>\n                </div>\n                <button onClick={() => setSelectedTicketId(null)} className=\"p-1 hover:bg-white/5 rounded text-white/40 cursor-pointer\"><X className=\"w-5 h-5\" /></button>\n              </div>\n\n              {/* Secure Enclave Diagnostics Bridge Visualizer */}\n              <div className=\"border border-white/5 rounded-xl bg-black/40 p-4 font-mono text-[10px] space-y-3 relative overflow-hidden\">\n                <style>{`\n                  @keyframes flowParticle {\n                    to { stroke-dashoffset: -20; }\n                  }\n                  .animate-flow-fast {\n                    stroke-dasharray: 6, 6;\n                    animation: flowParticle 0.6s linear infinite;\n                  }\n                  .animate-flow-normal {\n                    stroke-dasharray: 6, 6;\n                    animation: flowParticle 1.5s linear infinite;\n                  }\n                  .animate-flow-slow {\n                    stroke-dasharray: 6, 6;\n                    animation: flowParticle 3.5s linear infinite;\n                  }\n                `}</style>\n                \n                <div className=\"flex justify-between items-center text-[8.5px] text-white/40 uppercase tracking-wider\">\n                  <span>Enclave Telemetry Bridge</span>\n                  <span className=\"flex items-center gap-1\">\n                    <span className={`w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full ${selectedTicket.status === \"RESOLVED\" ? \"bg-white/20\" : selectedTicket.priority === \"P1\" ? \"bg-red-500 animate-ping\" : \"bg-cyan-400 animate-pulse\"}`} />\n                    <span className={selectedTicket.status === \"RESOLVED\" ? \"text-white/40\" : selectedTicket.priority === \"P1\" ? \"text-red-400 font-bold\" : \"text-cyan-400\"}>\n                      {selectedTicket.status === \"RESOLVED\" ? \"TERMINATED\" : `${selectedTicket.priority} STREAM ACTIVE`}\n                    </span>\n                  </span>\n                </div>\n\n                <div className=\"relative h-20 w-full flex items-center justify-center\">\n                  <svg className=\"w-full h-full overflow-visible\" viewBox=\"0 0 400 80\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n                    {/* Background Arc */}\n                    <path d=\"M 40 40 Q 200 10 360 40\" stroke=\"rgba(255,255,255,0.05)\" strokeWidth=\"3\" strokeLinecap=\"round\" />\n                    \n                    {/* Flow Arc */}\n                    {selectedTicket.status !== \"RESOLVED\" && (\n                      <path \n                        d=\"M 40 40 Q 200 10 360 40\" \n                        stroke={selectedTicket.status === \"HOLD\" ? \"#FBBF24\" : selectedTicket.priority === \"P1\" ? \"#F87171\" : \"#22D3EE\"} \n                        strokeWidth=\"1.5\" \n                        strokeLinecap=\"round\"\n                        className={selectedTicket.status === \"HOLD\" ? \"animate-flow-slow\" : selectedTicket.priority === \"P1\" ? \"animate-flow-fast\" : \"animate-flow-normal\"}\n                      />\n                    )}\n\n                    {/* Nodes */}\n                    {/* Client Node */}\n                    <g transform=\"translate(40, 40)\">\n                      <circle r=\"12\" fill=\"#070708\" stroke={selectedTicket.status === \"RESOLVED\" ? \"rgba(255,255,255,0.1)\" : selectedTicket.priority === \"P1\" ? \"#EF4444\" : \"#06B6D4\"} strokeWidth=\"1.5\" />\n                      <circle r=\"6\" fill={selectedTicket.status === \"RESOLVED\" ? \"rgba(255,255,255,0.2)\" : selectedTicket.priority === \"P1\" ? \"#EF4444\" : \"#06B6D4\"} className={selectedTicket.status !== \"RESOLVED\" ? \"animate-pulse\" : \"\"} />\n                      {/* Pulse ring for warning */}\n                      {selectedTicket.status !== \"RESOLVED\" && selectedTicket.priority === \"P1\" && (\n                        <circle r=\"18\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#EF4444\" strokeWidth=\"1\" className=\"animate-ping opacity-30\" />\n                      )}\n                    </g>\n\n                    {/* Admin Node */}\n                    <g transform=\"translate(360, 40)\">\n                      <circle r=\"12\" fill=\"#070708\" stroke={selectedTicket.status === \"RESOLVED\" ? \"rgba(255,255,255,0.1)\" : selectedTicket.assignedAgent === \"Unassigned\" ? \"#F59E0B\" : \"#10B981\"} strokeWidth=\"1.5\" />\n                      <circle r=\"6\" fill={selectedTicket.status === \"RESOLVED\" ? \"rgba(255,255,255,0.2)\" : selectedTicket.assignedAgent === \"Unassigned\" ? \"#F59E0B\" : \"#10B981\"} />\n                    </g>\n\n                    {/* Label tags inside SVG */}\n                    <text x=\"40\" y=\"68\" fill=\"rgba(255,255,255,0.4)\" fontSize=\"7\" fontFamily=\"monospace\" textAnchor=\"middle\">ENCLAVE</text>\n                    <text x=\"360\" y=\"68\" fill=\"rgba(255,255,255,0.4)\" fontSize=\"7\" fontFamily=\"monospace\" textAnchor=\"middle\">TERMINAL</text>\n                    \n                    {/* Bridge attestation status */}\n                    <rect x=\"150\" y=\"28\" width=\"100\" height=\"14\" rx=\"3\" fill=\"#070708\" stroke=\"rgba(255,255,255,0.1)\" />\n                    <text x=\"200\" y=\"37\" fill={selectedTicket.status === \"RESOLVED\" ? \"rgba(255,255,255,0.3)\" : \"#00FFC2\"} fontSize=\"6.5\" fontFamily=\"monospace\" textAnchor=\"middle\" fontWeight=\"bold\">\n                      {selectedTicket.status === \"RESOLVED\" ? \"ATTESTATION_OFF\" : \"TLS_1.3_SECURE\"}\n                    </text>\n                  </svg>\n                </div>\n\n                <div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 pt-1 border-t border-white/5 text-[9px] text-white/50\">\n                  <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n                    <div>CLIENT ENDPOINT: <span className=\"text-white font-bold\">{selectedTicket.client.split(\" [\")[0]}</span></div>\n                    <div>SEALING ENGINE: <span className=\"text-white font-mono font-bold\">Intel SGX v2</span></div>\n                  </div>\n                  <div className=\"space-y-1 text-right\">\n                    <div>OPERATIONAL NODE: <span className=\"text-white font-bold\">{selectedTicket.id}-GATEWAY</span></div>\n                    <div>TUNNEL LATENCY: <span className=\"text-emerald-400 font-bold\">{selectedTicket.priority === \"P1\" ? \"145ms (HIGH)\" : \"42ms (NOMINAL)\"}</span></div>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n\n              <div className=\"flex border-b border-white/5 font-mono text-[9.5px] select-none\">"}}}
